{"title_page": "Yorkshire Air Museum", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox museum\n |name          = Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Air Forces Memorial\n |image         = Elvington - YAM replica Wright Flyer 16-6-2015 10-46-53.JPG\n |caption       = Replica of a [[Wright Flyer]] at the museum\n |map_type      = \n |map_caption   = \n |coordinates   = {{coord|53.92480|-0.96531|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title,inline}}\n |established   = {{Start date|1986}}\n |dissolved     = \n |type          = [[Aviation museum]]\n |location      = Halifax Way, [[Elvington, City of York|Elvington]], York, YO41 4AU\n |visitors      = \n |director      = \n |curator       = \n |publictransit = \n |website       = {{URL|http://www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk|www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk}}\n}}\n{{OSM Location map\n| lat =53.95      <!-- lat and lon location for centre of map -->\n| lon =-1.09\n| float=right\n| zoom =10\n| width = 250        <!-- width and height of the frame. numeric input - do not add px -->\n| height = 250\n| caption = Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington, York\n| minimap = file\n| mini-file=York UK locator map.svg\n| mini-width=100\n| mini-height=73\n| minipog-x=64\n| minipog-y=47\n| scalemark =120\n\n| mark-lat =53.92480 <!-- lat and lon location for the marker -->\n| mark-lon =-0.96531\n|mark-size=10\n| label = Yorkshire Air Museum<!-- could add text here, but the map happens to already include it-->\n|label-size=10\n|label-color=black\n|label-pos=left\n| mark-title = Yorkshire Air Museum\n| mark-image = Elvington - YAM 16-6-2015 10-21-15.JPG   <!-- these three are used within the full screen linked page -->\n| mark-description = The Yorkshire Air Museum on the site of the former [[RAF Elvington]] airfield\n}}\nThe '''Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Air Forces Memorial''' is an air museum in [[England]] on the site of the former [[RAF Elvington]] airfield, a [[Second World War]] [[RAF Bomber Command]] station.  The museum was founded, and first opened to the public, in the early 1980s.\n\nThe museum is the largest independent air museum in [[United Kingdom|Britain]].<ref name=\"YorkshirePostHats\">{{cite news |title=Hats off to a century of air combat as RAF flypast marks anniversary |url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/latest-news/hats-off-to-a-century-of-air-combat-as-raf-flypast-marks-anniversary-1-9087172 |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=Yorkshire Post |date=28 March 2018}}</ref> It is also the only Allied Air Forces Memorial in Europe and has an international reputation and profile with established branches in Canada and France and the support of over 4,000 registered \"friends\" across the world.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hemmings|first1=Julie|title=Next generation renews air links across ocean|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/next-generation-renews-air-links-across-ocean-1-2608526|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Yorkshire Post|date=18 March 2009}}</ref> The museum is a Corporate Member of Friends of the Few ([[Battle of Britain Memorial, London|Battle of Britain Memorial]]) and the [[Royal Aeronautical Society]].\n\nThe Museum's principal activity is in education and the history of flight, through which it is involved with aerospace manufacturers and organisations via its long term \"Reach for the Sky\" project. This delivered the first [[Key Stage 2|KS2]] History of Aviation educational resource book to all 26,000 primary schools in UK, supported by RAeS and the Ministry of Transport.\n \nThe museum is expanding rapidly and received over 100,000 visitors in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ian Reed, director of the Yorkshire Air Museum and Visit York\u2019s York Ambassador Of The Year 2012|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/business/boss/9679904.Ian_Reed__director_of_the_Yorkshire_Air_Museum_and_Visit_York___s_York_Ambassador_Of_The_Year_2012/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=1 May 2012}}</ref> It has received many awards, such as: Top Specialist Attraction in UK - 2011 & 2015; Top Attraction in Yorkshire, Press Top Tourism Business; York Top Marketing Award and [[Winalot]] Top Dog Friendly Museum in UK.\n\n==The site==\n{{See|RAF Elvington}}\nThe {{convert|20|acre|m2|adj=on}} parkland site includes buildings and hangars, some of which are [[listed building|listed]]. It incorporates a {{convert|7|acre|m2|adj=on}} managed environment area and a [[Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs|DEFRA]] and [[Environment Agency]] supported self sustainability project called \"Nature of Flight\". The museum is situated next to a privately owned 10,000&nbsp;ft x 400 acre international standard runway. The site which has held the [[Yorkshire in Bloom]], Silver Gilt Award 3 times. \n\nWhilst the Royal Air Force carried on using the runway for aircraft landing and take off training until 1992, the buildings and hangars had long been abandoned. In 1983, a group started clearing the undergrowth and the site was ready to be unveiled as the Yorkshire Air Museum in 1986.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington, York|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/northyorkshire/purplepatch/articles/yorkshire_air_museum.shtml|website=BBC North Yorkshire|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Leadership and staffing==\nThe President of the Museum/Memorial is Air Chief Marshal Sir [[Stephen Dalton]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Battle Of Britain Commemoration Service and Parade at Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/4583831.Battle_Of_Britain_Commemoration_Service_and_Parade_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=7 September 2009}}</ref> and Vice Presidents include; the Chief of the Air Staff, Sir [[Andrew Pulford]]; Chief of the French Air Force, General [[Andr\u00e9 Lanata|Andre Lanata]]; Supreme Allied Commander NATO, General [[Denis Mercier]]; Archbishop of York, Dr [[John Sentamu]]; and TV Presenter, [[Jan Leeming]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hickling|first1=Michael|title=Breaking news on Jan\u2019s new flightpath|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/breaking-news-on-jan-s-new-flightpath-1-4380189|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Yorkshire Post|date=26 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt is operated by 149 staff, of which 130 are unpaid volunteers. A small operations team works closely together in a variety of specialist subjects from PR/marketing to Corporate Affairs and Museum Management.\n\n==Events==\nThe Museum undertakes several annual events each year within the general attraction / entertainment area as well as educational / academic events for specific audiences, plus several corporate events in association with companies such as Bentley, Porsche, banking, government agencies etc.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/1600873.Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=1 June 2007}}</ref> The unique annual Allied Air Forces Memorial Day takes place in September.\n\n==Museum features==\nThe Museum has around 50 aircraft<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Forces Memorial|url=http://www.moviemakersguide.com/data/y/yoram0733/yoram0733a.htm|website=Moviemakers Guide.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> spanning the development of aviation from 1853 up to the latest GR4 Tornado.<ref>{{cite web|title=Allied Forecs memorial & Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkshire.com/view/culture/york/allied-air-forces-memorial-and-yorkshire-air-museum-1095030|website=Yorkshire.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> Several aircraft including Victor, Nimrod, Buccaneer, Sea Devon, SE5a, Eastchurch Kitten; DC3 Dakota; are kept live and operated on special \"Thunder Days\" during the year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thunder Day at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/10344163.Thunder_Day_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=10 April 2013}}</ref> Over 20 historic vehicles and a Registered Archive containing over 500,000 historic artefacts and documents are also preserved at the Museum, which is also the Official Archive for the National Aircrew Association and National Air Gunners Association. It is nationally registered and accredited through DCMS/Arts Council England and is a registered charity.\n[[File:Elvington - YAM 16-6-2015 10-21-15.JPG|thumb|]]\n\nA permanent exhibition on [[RAF Bomber Command]] was opened at the museum by life member, [[David Jason|Sir David Jason]]. In 2010 a new exhibition called \"Pioneers of Aviation\", and funded by the [[Heritage Lottery Fund]], was opened featuring the lives and achievements of Sir [[George Cayley]], Sir [[Barnes Wallis]], [[Robert Blackburn (aviation pioneer)|Robert Blackburn]], [[Nevil Shute]] and [[Amy Johnson]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mead|first1=Helen|title=The shy's the limit at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.cravenherald.co.uk/news/9515740.The_sky___s_the_limit_at_the_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Craven Herald & Pioneer|date=7 February 2012}}</ref>\n\nPrincipal on-site businesses include: Restaurant, Publishing, Retail Shop, Fire Service, Events, Aircraft Operation Engineering Workshops, Archives and Corporate Business Suite. The museum produces its own films and publications and is also a popular location for TV and film companies.\n\n* Building 1. Airborne Forces Display & [[No. 609 Squadron RAF|No. 609 (West Riding) Squadron]] Room.\n* Building 2. Uniform Display.\n* Building 3. Air Gunners' Exhibition.\n* Building 4. Archives & Reference Library.\n* Building 5. Museum Shop.\n* Building 7. Memorial Garden.\n* Building 8. Museum HQ, Main Entrance.\n* Building 9. Against the Odds - History of Bomber Command, [[RAF Regiment]] Exhibition, [[No. 77 Squadron RAF|77 Squadron]] Exhibition and Digital Astra Cinema\n* Building 10. Elvington Corporate Room.\n* Building 11. Museum [[NAAFI]] Restaurant.\n* Building 12. Control Tower.\n* Building 13. French Officers' Mess.\n* Building 14. Airmens Billet and Station MT Display.\n* Building 15. Royal Observer Corp.\n* Building 16. Signal Square.\n* Building 17. Hangar T2 Main Aircraft exhibition.\n* Building 18. Archive & Collections Building\n* Building 19. [[Handley Page]] Aircraft Workshop.\n* Building 20. Pioneer of Aviation Exhibition\n\n==Military vehicles==\n;Second World War\n* 1937 Ford Model E\n* 1940 \"[[Tilly (vehicle)|Tilly]]\" Standard 12&nbsp;hp Mkl RAF Utility Vehicle\n* 1941 [[Chevrolet]] 4x4 CMP\n* 1942 [[Austin K2]] [[NAAFI]] Wagon\n\n;Cold War\n[[File:YAM Range Rover Airport Crash Tender - Elvington - BB.jpg|thumb|The museum's [[TACR2]]]]\n* 1947 Commer one and a half deck airport coach\n* 1949 Citroen 11BL\n* 1948 [[David Brown (entrepreneur)|David Brown]] VIG.2 Aircraft Tractor\n* 1949 David Brown VIG.3 Aircraft Tractor\n* 1951 David Brown GP Airfield Tractor\n* 1953 [[Alvis Saracen]] 12ton APC\n* 1953 [[Austin Champ]] Cargo 4x4 General Purpose Vehicle\n* 1956 [[Green Goddess]] Self Propelled Pump\n* 1958 [[Commer]] Q4 Bikini Fire Pump Unit\n* 1958 Lansing Aircraft Carrier Type Tug\n* 1959 [[Daimler Ferret]] ASC MK.2/3/7\n* 1966 [[Chieftain (tank)|Chieftain]] Main Battle Tank\n* 1970 Douglas P3 nuclear aircraft 25 tonne tug \n* 1971 Pathfinder Fire Engine 35ton (ex. [[Manchester Airport]])\n* 1972 [[TACR2]] Range Rover - 6 wheeled fast response fire unit\n* 1974 GMC 6 wheeled fast response airfield fire truck\n* 1976 Dennis Mercury 17.5 tonne aircraft tug\n\n==Aircraft collection==\nThe following is a list of aircraft on display at the Yorkshire Air Museum.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hitchens|first1=Frank|title=Aircraft museums of the United Kingdom|date=2016|publisher=Andrews UK|isbn=9781785384516|pages=169-170}}</ref>\n;Pioneers\n1853 Replica [[George Cayley]] Glider<br />\n1903 Replica [[Wright Flyer]]<br />\n1911 Replica [[Blackburn Mercury]] Monoplane BAPC-130\n\n;First World War\n1913 Replica [[Avro 504]] H1968 BAPC-42<br />\n1914 Replica [[Royal Aircraft Factory BE.2]] 6232<br />\n1917 Replica [[Port Victoria P.V.8]] Grain Kitten<br />\n1917 Replica [[Royal Aircraft Factory SE.5]] F943\n\n;Interwar\n1933 [[Mignet HM.14]] ''Pou-du-Ciel'' BAPC-76\n\n;Second World War\n1935 [[Avro Anson]] VV901<br />\n1937 Replica Messerschmitt Bf-109G6<br />\n1938 Replica [[Supermarine Spitfire]]<br />\n1940 [[Handley Page Halifax]] LV907<br />\n\n1942 [[Waco Hadrian]] 237123 BAPC-157<br />\n1944 [[Gloster Meteor]] WK864, WS788\n[[File:Halifax Bomber Yorkshire Air Museum.jpg|thumb|center|600px|\"Friday the 13th\" original reconstruction of [[Handley Page Halifax]] - part of Yorkshire Air Museum's [[Second World War]] aircraft collection]]\n{{clear}}\n;Cold War\n* 1948 [[De Havilland Sea Devon|De Havilland Devon C.2]] VP967\n* 1950 [[Westland Dragonfly|Westland Dragonfly HR.5]] WH991\n* 1951 [[English Electric Canberra|English Electric Canberra T.4]] WH846\n* 1952 [[Canadair CT-133 Silver Star]]\n* 1952 [[De Havilland Venom|De Havilland Venom NF.3]] WX788\n* 1953 [[Fairey Gannet AEW.3]] XL502\n* 1954 [[English Electric Lightning|English Electric Lightning F.6]] XS903\n* 1954 [[BAC Jet Provost|BAC Jet Provost T.4]] XP640\n* 1956 [[Gloster Javelin|Gloster Javelin FAW.9]] XH767\n* 1956 [[Hawker Hunter|Hawker Hunter T.7]] N268, XL572\n* 1956 [[Saro Skeeter]] G-AWSV\n* (Taxiable) 1958 [[Handley Page Victor|Handley Page Victor K.2]] XL231<ref>{{cite news|title=Aircraft celebrates birthday at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/3873180.Aircraft_celebrates_birthday_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=24 November 2008}}</ref>\n* 1961 [[Dassault Mirage III]] 538\n* (Taxiable) 1962 [[Blackburn Buccaneer|Blackburn Buccaneer S.2]] XN974\n* 1964 Blackburn Buccaneer S.2B XX901\n* 1964 [[Dassault Mirage IV|Dassault Mirage IVA]] The only one outside of France and was gifted to the museum by the French government in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nuclear bomber begins trip to Yorkshire|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-york-north-yorkshire-39407024|accessdate=7 June 2017|work=BBC News|date=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n* 1969 [[Hawker Siddeley Harrier|British Aerospace Harrier GR.3]] XV748\n* 1969 [[Hawker Siddeley Nimrod|British Aerospace Nimrod MR.2]] XV250\n* 1980 [[Panavia Tornado|Panavia Tornado GR.1]] ZA354\n* 2003 [[Panavia Tornado|Panavia Tornado GR.4]] XZ631\n\n;Civilian Aircraft\n1961 [[Beagle Terrier]] TJ704\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category-inline|Yorkshire Air Museum}}\n* [http://www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk Yorkshire Air Museum]\n\n{{British Aviation Museums}}\n\n[[Category:Aerospace museums in England]]\n[[Category:Museums in York]]\n[[Category:Museums established in 1986]]\n[[Category:World War II museums in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Military aviation museums in England]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox museum\n |name          = Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Air Forces Memorial\n |image         = Elvington - YAM replica Wright Flyer 16-6-2015 10-46-53.JPG\n |caption       = Replica of a [[Wright Flyer]] at the museum\n |map_type      = \n |map_caption   = \n |coordinates   = {{coord|53.92480|-0.96531|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title,inline}}\n |established   = {{Start date|1986}}\n |dissolved     = \n |type          = [[Aviation museum]]\n |location      = Halifax Way, [[Elvington, City of York|Elvington]], York, YO41 4AU\n |visitors      = \n |director      = \n |curator       = \n |publictransit = \n |website       = {{URL|http://www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk|www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk}}\n}}\n{{OSM Location map\n| lat =53.95      <!-- lat and lon location for centre of map -->\n| lon =-1.09\n| float=right\n| zoom =10\n| width = 250        <!-- width and height of the frame. numeric input - do not add px -->\n| height = 250\n| caption = Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington, York\n| minimap = file\n| mini-file=York UK locator map.svg\n| mini-width=100\n| mini-height=73\n| minipog-x=64\n| minipog-y=47\n| scalemark =120\n\n| mark-lat =53.92480 <!-- lat and lon location for the marker -->\n| mark-lon =-0.96531\n|mark-size=10\n| label = Yorkshire Air Museum<!-- could add text here, but the map happens to already include it-->\n|label-size=10\n|label-color=black\n|label-pos=left\n| mark-title = Yorkshire Air Museum\n| mark-image = Elvington - YAM 16-6-2015 10-21-15.JPG   <!-- these three are used within the full screen linked page -->\n| mark-description = The Yorkshire Air Museum on the site of the former [[RAF Elvington]] airfield\n}}\nThe '''Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Air Forces Memorial''' is an air museum in [[England]] on the site of the former [[RAF Elvington]] airfield, a [[Second World War]] [[RAF Bomber Command]] station.  The museum was founded, and first opened to the public, in the early 1980s.\n\nThe museum is the largest independent air museum in [[United Kingdom|Britain]].<ref name=\"YorkshirePostHats\">{{cite news |title=Hats off to a century of air combat as RAF flypast marks anniversary |url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/latest-news/hats-off-to-a-century-of-air-combat-as-raf-flypast-marks-anniversary-1-9087172 |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=Yorkshire Post |date=28 March 2018}}</ref> It is also the only Allied Air Forces Memorial in Europe and has an international reputation and profile with established branches in Canada and France and the support of over 4,000 registered \"friends\" across the world.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hemmings|first1=Julie|title=Next generation renews air links across ocean|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/next-generation-renews-air-links-across-ocean-1-2608526|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Yorkshire Post|date=18 March 2009}}</ref> The museum is a Corporate Member of Friends of the Few ([[Battle of Britain Memorial, London|Battle of Britain Memorial]]) and the [[Royal Aeronautical Society]].\n\nThe Museum's principal activity is in education and the history of flight, through which it is involved with aerospace manufacturers and organisations via its long term \"Reach for the Sky\" project. This delivered the first [[Key Stage 2|KS2]] History of Aviation educational resource book to all 26,000 primary schools in UK, supported by RAeS and the Ministry of Transport.\n \nThe museum is expanding rapidly and received over 100,000 visitors in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ian Reed, director of the Yorkshire Air Museum and Visit York\u2019s York Ambassador Of The Year 2012|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/business/boss/9679904.Ian_Reed__director_of_the_Yorkshire_Air_Museum_and_Visit_York___s_York_Ambassador_Of_The_Year_2012/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=1 May 2012}}</ref> It has received many awards, such as: Top Specialist Attraction in UK - 2011 & 2015; Top Attraction in Yorkshire, Press Top Tourism Business; York Top Marketing Award and [[Winalot]] Top Dog Friendly Museum in UK.\n\n==The site==\n{{See|RAF Elvington}}\nThe {{convert|20|acre|m2|adj=on}} parkland site includes buildings and hangars, some of which are [[listed building|listed]]. It incorporates a {{convert|7|acre|m2|adj=on}} managed environment area and a [[Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs|DEFRA]] and [[Environment Agency]] supported self sustainability project called \"Nature of Flight\". The museum is situated next to a 10,000&nbsp;ft x 400 acre international standard runway. The site which has held the [[Yorkshire in Bloom]], Silver Gilt Award 3 times. \n\nWhilst the Royal Air Force carried on using the runway for aircraft landing and take off training until 1992, the buildings and hangars had long been abandoned. In 1983, a group started clearing the undergrowth and the site was ready to be unveiled as the Yorkshire Air Museum in 1986.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington, York|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/northyorkshire/purplepatch/articles/yorkshire_air_museum.shtml|website=BBC North Yorkshire|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Leadership and staffing==\nThe President of the Museum/Memorial is Air Chief Marshal Sir [[Stephen Dalton]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Battle Of Britain Commemoration Service and Parade at Yorkshire Air Museum, Elvington|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/4583831.Battle_Of_Britain_Commemoration_Service_and_Parade_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=7 September 2009}}</ref> and Vice Presidents include; the Chief of the Air Staff, Sir [[Andrew Pulford]]; Chief of the French Air Force, General [[Andr\u00e9 Lanata|Andre Lanata]]; Supreme Allied Commander NATO, General [[Denis Mercier]]; Archbishop of York, Dr [[John Sentamu]]; and TV Presenter, [[Jan Leeming]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hickling|first1=Michael|title=Breaking news on Jan\u2019s new flightpath|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/breaking-news-on-jan-s-new-flightpath-1-4380189|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Yorkshire Post|date=26 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt is operated by 149 staff, of which 130 are unpaid volunteers. A small operations team works closely together in a variety of specialist subjects from PR/marketing to Corporate Affairs and Museum Management.\n\n==Events==\nThe Museum undertakes several annual events each year within the general attraction / entertainment area as well as educational / academic events for specific audiences, plus several corporate events in association with companies such as Bentley, Porsche, banking, government agencies etc.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/1600873.Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=1 June 2007}}</ref> The unique annual Allied Air Forces Memorial Day takes place in September.\n\n==Museum features==\nThe Museum has around 50 aircraft<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorkshire Air Museum & Allied Forces Memorial|url=http://www.moviemakersguide.com/data/y/yoram0733/yoram0733a.htm|website=Moviemakers Guide.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> spanning the development of aviation from 1853 up to the latest GR4 Tornado.<ref>{{cite web|title=Allied Forecs memorial & Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkshire.com/view/culture/york/allied-air-forces-memorial-and-yorkshire-air-museum-1095030|website=Yorkshire.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> Several aircraft including Victor, Nimrod, Buccaneer, Sea Devon, SE5a, Eastchurch Kitten; DC3 Dakota; are kept live and operated on special \"Thunder Days\" during the year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thunder Day at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/10344163.Thunder_Day_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=10 April 2013}}</ref> Over 20 historic vehicles and a Registered Archive containing over 500,000 historic artefacts and documents are also preserved at the Museum, which is also the Official Archive for the National Aircrew Association and National Air Gunners Association. It is nationally registered and accredited through DCMS/Arts Council England and is a registered charity.\n[[File:Elvington - YAM 16-6-2015 10-21-15.JPG|thumb|]]\n\nA permanent exhibition on [[RAF Bomber Command]] was opened at the museum by life member, [[David Jason|Sir David Jason]]. In 2010 a new exhibition called \"Pioneers of Aviation\", and funded by the [[Heritage Lottery Fund]], was opened featuring the lives and achievements of Sir [[George Cayley]], Sir [[Barnes Wallis]], [[Robert Blackburn (aviation pioneer)|Robert Blackburn]], [[Nevil Shute]] and [[Amy Johnson]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mead|first1=Helen|title=The shy's the limit at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.cravenherald.co.uk/news/9515740.The_sky___s_the_limit_at_the_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=Craven Herald & Pioneer|date=7 February 2012}}</ref>\n\nPrincipal on-site businesses include: Restaurant, Publishing, Retail Shop, Fire Service, Events, Aircraft Operation Engineering Workshops, Archives and Corporate Business Suite. The museum produces its own films and publications and is also a popular location for TV and film companies.\n\n* Building 1. Airborne Forces Display & [[No. 609 Squadron RAF|No. 609 (West Riding) Squadron]] Room.\n* Building 2. Uniform Display.\n* Building 3. Air Gunners' Exhibition.\n* Building 4. Archives & Reference Library.\n* Building 5. Museum Shop.\n* Building 7. Memorial Garden.\n* Building 8. Museum HQ, Main Entrance.\n* Building 9. Against the Odds - History of Bomber Command, [[RAF Regiment]] Exhibition, [[No. 77 Squadron RAF|77 Squadron]] Exhibition and Digital Astra Cinema\n* Building 10. Elvington Corporate Room.\n* Building 11. Museum [[NAAFI]] Restaurant.\n* Building 12. Control Tower.\n* Building 13. French Officers' Mess.\n* Building 14. Airmens Billet and Station MT Display.\n* Building 15. Royal Observer Corp.\n* Building 16. Signal Square.\n* Building 17. Hangar T2 Main Aircraft exhibition.\n* Building 18. Archive & Collections Building\n* Building 19. [[Handley Page]] Aircraft Workshop.\n* Building 20. Pioneer of Aviation Exhibition\n\n==Military vehicles==\n;Second World War\n* 1937 Ford Model E\n* 1940 \"[[Tilly (vehicle)|Tilly]]\" Standard 12&nbsp;hp Mkl RAF Utility Vehicle\n* 1941 [[Chevrolet]] 4x4 CMP\n* 1942 [[Austin K2]] [[NAAFI]] Wagon\n\n;Cold War\n[[File:YAM Range Rover Airport Crash Tender - Elvington - BB.jpg|thumb|The museum's [[TACR2]]]]\n* 1947 Commer one and a half deck airport coach\n* 1949 Citroen 11BL\n* 1948 [[David Brown (entrepreneur)|David Brown]] VIG.2 Aircraft Tractor\n* 1949 David Brown VIG.3 Aircraft Tractor\n* 1951 David Brown GP Airfield Tractor\n* 1953 [[Alvis Saracen]] 12ton APC\n* 1953 [[Austin Champ]] Cargo 4x4 General Purpose Vehicle\n* 1956 [[Green Goddess]] Self Propelled Pump\n* 1958 [[Commer]] Q4 Bikini Fire Pump Unit\n* 1958 Lansing Aircraft Carrier Type Tug\n* 1959 [[Daimler Ferret]] ASC MK.2/3/7\n* 1966 [[Chieftain (tank)|Chieftain]] Main Battle Tank\n* 1970 Douglas P3 nuclear aircraft 25 tonne tug \n* 1971 Pathfinder Fire Engine 35ton (ex. [[Manchester Airport]])\n* 1972 [[TACR2]] Range Rover - 6 wheeled fast response fire unit\n* 1974 GMC 6 wheeled fast response airfield fire truck\n* 1976 Dennis Mercury 17.5 tonne aircraft tug\n\n==Aircraft collection==\nThe following is a list of aircraft on display at the Yorkshire Air Museum.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hitchens|first1=Frank|title=Aircraft museums of the United Kingdom|date=2016|publisher=Andrews UK|isbn=9781785384516|pages=169-170}}</ref>\n;Pioneers\n1853 Replica [[George Cayley]] Glider<br />\n1903 Replica [[Wright Flyer]]<br />\n1911 Replica [[Blackburn Mercury]] Monoplane BAPC-130\n\n;First World War\n1913 Replica [[Avro 504]] H1968 BAPC-42<br />\n1914 Replica [[Royal Aircraft Factory BE.2]] 6232<br />\n1917 Replica [[Port Victoria P.V.8]] Grain Kitten<br />\n1917 Replica [[Royal Aircraft Factory SE.5]] F943\n\n;Interwar\n1933 [[Mignet HM.14]] ''Pou-du-Ciel'' BAPC-76\n\n;Second World War\n1935 [[Avro Anson]] VV901<br />\n1937 Replica Messerschmitt Bf-109G6<br />\n1938 Replica [[Supermarine Spitfire]]<br />\n1940 [[Handley Page Halifax]] LV907<br />\n\n1942 [[Waco Hadrian]] 237123 BAPC-157<br />\n1944 [[Gloster Meteor]] WK864, WS788\n[[File:Halifax Bomber Yorkshire Air Museum.jpg|thumb|center|600px|\"Friday the 13th\" original reconstruction of [[Handley Page Halifax]] - part of Yorkshire Air Museum's [[Second World War]] aircraft collection]]\n{{clear}}\n;Cold War\n* 1948 [[De Havilland Sea Devon|De Havilland Devon C.2]] VP967\n* 1950 [[Westland Dragonfly|Westland Dragonfly HR.5]] WH991\n* 1951 [[English Electric Canberra|English Electric Canberra T.4]] WH846\n* 1952 [[Canadair CT-133 Silver Star]]\n* 1952 [[De Havilland Venom|De Havilland Venom NF.3]] WX788\n* 1953 [[Fairey Gannet AEW.3]] XL502\n* 1954 [[English Electric Lightning|English Electric Lightning F.6]] XS903\n* 1954 [[BAC Jet Provost|BAC Jet Provost T.4]] XP640\n* 1956 [[Gloster Javelin|Gloster Javelin FAW.9]] XH767\n* 1956 [[Hawker Hunter|Hawker Hunter T.7]] N268, XL572\n* 1956 [[Saro Skeeter]] G-AWSV\n* (Taxiable) 1958 [[Handley Page Victor|Handley Page Victor K.2]] XL231<ref>{{cite news|title=Aircraft celebrates birthday at Yorkshire Air Museum|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/3873180.Aircraft_celebrates_birthday_at_Yorkshire_Air_Museum/|accessdate=20 July 2016|work=York Press|date=24 November 2008}}</ref>\n* 1961 [[Dassault Mirage III]] 538\n* (Taxiable) 1962 [[Blackburn Buccaneer|Blackburn Buccaneer S.2]] XN974\n* 1964 Blackburn Buccaneer S.2B XX901\n* 1964 [[Dassault Mirage IV|Dassault Mirage IVA]] The only one outside of France and was gifted to the museum by the French government in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nuclear bomber begins trip to Yorkshire|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-york-north-yorkshire-39407024|accessdate=7 June 2017|work=BBC News|date=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n* 1969 [[Hawker Siddeley Harrier|British Aerospace Harrier GR.3]] XV748\n* 1969 [[Hawker Siddeley Nimrod|British Aerospace Nimrod MR.2]] XV250\n* 1980 [[Panavia Tornado|Panavia Tornado GR.1]] ZA354\n* 2003 [[Panavia Tornado|Panavia Tornado GR.4]] XZ631\n\n;Civilian Aircraft\n1961 [[Beagle Terrier]] TJ704\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category-inline|Yorkshire Air Museum}}\n* [http://www.yorkshireairmuseum.co.uk Yorkshire Air Museum]\n\n{{British Aviation Museums}}\n\n[[Category:Aerospace museums in England]]\n[[Category:Museums in York]]\n[[Category:Museums established in 1986]]\n[[Category:World War II museums in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Military aviation museums in England]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "Ian Reed", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eThe site", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yorkshire_Air_Museum"}
{"title_page": "The Circle (Brazilian TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian reality television show}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name             = The Circle Brazil\n| image                 = The Circle Brazil (poster).jpeg\n| caption               = Promotional poster for the series\n| genre                 = [[Reality television|Reality competition]]\n| creative_director     = \n| presenter             = [[Giovanna Ewbank]]\n| narrated              = \n| country               = [[Brazil]]\n| theme_music_composer  = \n| opentheme             = \n| language              = Portuguese\n| num_seasons           = 1\n| num_episodes          = 12\n| executive_producer    = \n| camera                = \n| runtime               = 39\u201361 minutes\n| channel               = [[Netflix]]\n| company               = [[Studio Lambert]]\n| distributor           = \n| picture_format        = \n| audio_format          = \n| first_aired           = {{Start date|2020|3|11|df=yes}}\n| last_aired            = {{End date|2020|3|25|df=yes}}\n| related               = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[The Circle (British TV series)|The Circle UK]]''\n* ''[[The Circle (American TV series)|The Circle US]]''\n* ''[[The Circle (French TV series)|The Circle France]]''\n}}\n| website               = https://www.thecirclecasting.com/brasil\n}}\n\n'''''The Circle Brazil''''' (also known as '''''The Circle Brasil''''' in [[Brazil]]) is a Brazilian [[Reality television|reality competition]] show, produced by [[Studio Lambert]] and Motion Content Group which will be launched on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/series/noticia/2018/12/netflix-fara-versao-brasileira-do-reality-britanico-circle.html |title= Netflix far\u00e1 vers\u00e3o brasileira do reality brit\u00e2nico 'The circle' |website=[[O Globo]] |language=Portuguese |date=19 December 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2019}}</ref> It premiered on 11 March 2020 and ended on 25 March as part of a three-week event.<ref name=\"teaser\">{{cite web |author1=Netflix Brasil |title=THE CIRCLE BRASIL COM GIOVANNA EWBANK \u2013 TEASER \u2013 NETFLIX BRASIL |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z_59QUGpch4 |website=youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=1 March 2020 |language=Portuguese |date=27 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Along with ''The Circle Brazil'', Netflix also released separate versions of ''[[The Circle (franchise)|The Circle]]'' in the [[United States]] and [[France]].<ref name=\"hollywood_reporter\">{{cite web |last1=Elise Sandberg |first1=Bryn |title=Netflix to Adapt U.K. Reality Series 'The Circle' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/netflix-adapt-uk-reality-series-circle-1150330 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=6 June 2019}}</ref> ''The Circle Brazil'' will be the first Brazilian reality TV show on Netflix.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Castro |first1=Daniel |title=Al\u00e9m de Gagliasso, Giovanna Ewbank \u00e9 contratada pela Netflix para comandar reality |url=https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/alem-de-gagliasso-giovanna-ewbank-e-contratada-pela-netflix-para-comandar-reality-32973 |website=noticiasdatv.uol.com.br |publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV por Daniel Castro |accessdate=1 February 2020 |language=Portuguese |date=27 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The show bills itself as a game based around social media, with the concept that \"anyone can be anyone in The Circle\". It has been compared to ''[[Big Brother (franchise)|Big Brother]]'' and ''[[Catfish: The TV Show|Catfish]]'' in format.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Peter |title=Netflix Remakes Studio Lambert\u2019s British Reality Series 'The Circle' In The U.S. & Two Other Global Markets |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/netflix-the-circle-1202478763/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nMarina Gregory won the first season of ''The Circle Brazil'' and the {{BRL|300000|link=yes}} prize that came along with it. Rayssa \"Ray\" Santos was the runner-up.\n\n== Format ==\nThe contestants, or \"players\", move into the same apartment building. However, the contestants do not meet face-to-face during the course of the competition, as they each live in their own individual apartment. They communicate solely using their profiles on a specially-designed [[social media]] app that gives them the ability to portray themselves in any way they choose. Players can thus opt to present themselves as a completely different personality to the other players, a tactic otherwise known as [[catfishing]]; for example, one male player in the first season presented himself as a female identity, while another female contestant used photos of a woman she felt was more attractive.<ref name=\"polygon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/entertainment/2020/1/10/21058661/the-circle-review-netflix-new-reality-show-catfishing|title=Netflix's The Circle is the sweetest reality show about catfishing|first=Ben|last=Kuchera|language=en-us|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=10 January 2020|work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>\n\nIn each episode, the contestants \"rate\" one another from first to last place. At the end of the ratings, their average ratings are revealed to one another from lowest to highest. Normally, the two highest-rated players become \"Influencers\", while the remaining players will be at risk of being \"blocked\" by the Influencers. However, occasionally there may be a twist to the blocking process \u2013 varying from the lowest rating players being instantly blocked, the identity of the influencers being a secret, or multiple players being blocked at one time. Blocked players are eliminated from the game, but are given the opportunity to meet one player still in the game in-person. Then, the day after a blocking, a video message is shown to the remaining players to reveal if they were real or fake.<ref name=\"polygon\"/>\n\nDuring the season finale, the contestants rate each other one final time, where the highest rated player wins the game and {{BRL|300000|link=yes}} ({{USD|67000}}).<ref name=\"teaser\"/>\n\n== Players ==\nA total of 14 players were selected from the \"20\u201325 individuals\" being cleared to appear on the show, with the remaining people never leaving standby status and not appearing on the show.<ref name=\"variety interview 1\">{{cite web |last1=Turchiano |first1=Danielle |title='The Circle' Boss on Connecting 'People Who Otherwise Might Not Have Come into Contact with Each Other' \u2014 And Catfishing |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/features/the-circle-netflix-american-tim-harcourt-catfish-interview-1203449625/ |website=variety.com |publisher=Variety |accessdate=2 January 2020 |date=1 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The players' profiles were revealed as they introduced themselves on-screen during an episode.<ref name=\"insider\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.craveyoutv.com/exclusive-interview-whats-next-for-best-friend-bill-from-the-circle/|title=Exclusive Interview: What's Next for Best Friend Bill from 'The Circle'|last=Buczak|first=Lizzy|date=2020-02-25|website=CraveyouTV TV Show Recaps, TV Reviews, Spoilers, Interviews|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Name\n! Age\n! Hometown\n! Playing as\n! Entered\n! Exit\n! Status\n|-\n| Ana Carla Medeiros\n| 22\n| [[Campina Grande]], [[Para\u00edba]]\n| Herself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 2\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Rob Vulcan\n| 34\n| [[Sorocaba]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| \"Julia\", a single and [[Bisexuality|bisexual]] 34-year-old\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 3\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Gabriel \"Gaybol\" Cardoso\n| 26\n| [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| Himself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 5\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Paloma \"Loma\" Lisboa\n| 26\n| [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| \"Lucas\", a sexy straight 25-year-old male \n| Episode 1\n| Episode 6\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Jo\u00e3o Akel\n| 20\n| [[Arax\u00e1]], [[Minas Gerais]]\n| Himself, but a 30-years-old dietician\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 9\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Lorayne Oliver\n| 22\n| [[Realeza]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]]\n| Herself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 10\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Renan Marconi\n| 30\n| [[Maring\u00e1]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]]\n| Himself, but a single 26-year-old\n| Episode 9\n| Episode 10\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Rafael \"Raf\" Vilar\n| 37\n| [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]]\n| \"Ana\", a [[Bisexuality|bisexual]] 35-year-old writer\n| Episode 7\n| Episode 11\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Lucas Blazute\n| 30\n| [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Twin brothers playing jointly as 27-year-old female \"Luma\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Episode 2\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|Episode 12}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | {{nowrap|Fifth place}}\n|-\n| Marcel Blazute\n| 30\n| [[Rio Branco, Acre|Rio Branco]], [[Acre (state)|Acre]]\n|-\n| Raphael Dumaresq\n| 24\n| [[Natal, Rio Grande do Norte|Natal]], [[Rio Grande do Norte]]\n| Himself\n| Episode 1\n| {{nowrap|Episode 12}}\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | {{nowrap|Fourth place}}\n|-\n| Jo\u00e3o Paulo \"JP\" Gadelha\n| 31\n| [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]]\n| Himself, but 28-years-old\n| Episode 1\n| {{nowrap|Episode 12}}\n| style=\"background:tan;\" | {{nowrap|Third place}}\n|-\n| Rayssa \"Ray\" Santos\n| 22\n| [[Manaus]], [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]]\n| Herself, but a single 25-year-old\n| Episode 4\n| {{nowrap|Episode 12}}\n| style=\"background:silver;\" | {{nowrap|Runner-up}}\n|-style=\"background:lavender;\"\n| '''Marina Gregory'''\n| '''25'''\n| '''[[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]]'''\n| '''Herself, but a 22-year-old singer'''\n| '''{{nowrap|Episode 1}}'''\n| '''{{nowrap|Episode 12}}'''\n| style=\"background:gold;\" | '''Winner'''\n|}\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table\n| total_width=100\n| background=#7CA1BE\n| overall=4\n| season=4\n| title=30\n| airdate=20\n| episodes=\n{{Episode table/part|p=Week 1|c=#7CA1BE|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = Welcome to The Circle\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|11|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The first nine players entered The Circle and were tasked with creating their profiles, including their age, relationship status, a short [[biography|bio]], and a profile picture. Immediately after, the players had to rank the other players from first to eighth bases on their first impressions of their profiles. The two players who ranked first and second would become The Circle Influencers, making the decision on whom they should block from The Circle. When the ratings were revealed, Dumaresq and Marina received first and second place, respectively. They went up to the Blue Room where they made the decision on who to block.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Welcome to The Circle|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062047?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C0%2Ca0e5085b-0ba6-45c7-9a9f-72b79ecb3a50-29101660%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=11 March 2020|season=1|number=1}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = House Party\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|11|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Dumaresq and Marina decided to block Ana Carla. As part of the format of the game, Ana Carla made her way to meet one of her fellow players face-to-face. She visited Dumaresq where she confronted him on calling her a catfish.\n\n*'''Game''': The next day, the players played an informal game where The Circle showed all the players an [[astrology]] chart and had the players guess what [[zodiac sign]] each of the other players were.\n\nThat night, there was a \"festa\" or party. The players all got a package at their door full of clothes they would wear to a carnival. Also in the box was ingredients and a recipe on how to make a [[caipirinha]]. Then, music was played throughout the apartments and the players started to dance. However, during the party, two twin brothers joined The Circle, playing as one player.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=House Party|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062048?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C1%2Cb57813d8-ab51-4a8d-9ce3-7e0eace81d9a-28553664%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=11 March 2020|season=1|number=2}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Follow the Dance\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|11|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The twins, who were revealed to be Lucas & Marcel, played jointly as a woman named Luma. They created their profile for The Circle, and joined the party. Before viewing Lucas & Marcel's profile, the players were allowed to post their best carnival photo as a new photo on the profile. While they were posting their photos, Lucas & Marcel were able to view all the other profiles. After every player posted their carnival photo, Lucas & Marcel posted their own photo, officially revealing Lucas & Marcel to the players.\n\nWhen Lucas & Marcel's photo is shown to the players, Rob immediately comments that they are accepting of [[transgender|transgender people]] despite that neither the photos Lucas & Marcel are using, nor the description on Lucas & Marcel's profile, suggests that she would be transgender. The next day, Rob asks Lucas & Marcel if their [[birth certificate]] has male or female on it, again hinting that she is transgender. This confuses many players since they did not think she was transgender. Lucas & Marcel say she is a woman and that female is written on her birth certificate.\n*'''Game (\"Segue o Baile\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Follow the Dance\")''': Lucas & Marcel had to perform different dance moves and the players, one at a time, had to guess which dance they were doing. The players who guessed the right dance move got coconut water and a certificate stating that they have excellent skills in recognizing dance styles.\nAfter the game, rating started. As new players, Lucas & Marcel could rate, but couldn't be rated. Lorayne and Marina were rated first and second respectively, making them Influencers. They decided to block Rob.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Follow the Dance|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062049?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C2%2Cb57813d8-ab51-4a8d-9ce3-7e0eace81d9a-28553664%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=11 March 2020|season=1|number=3}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Opinion Poll\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|11|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Rob went to Marina's apartment. The next morning, the newsfeed was updated with a video from Rob, revealing to all the players that he was a catfish.\n*'''Game (\"Pesquisa de Opini\u00e3o\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Opinion Poll\")''': The Circle gave the players five categories (sexiest, two-faced, biggest player, trustworthy, and most likely to be a catfish); the players had to choose which player fit the category the most. After everyone answered the questions, the poll results were announced.\nAfter the game, Ray entered The Circle.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Opinion Poll|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062050?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C3%2Cb57813d8-ab51-4a8d-9ce3-7e0eace81d9a-28553664%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=11 March 2020|season=1|number=3}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|p=Week 2|c=#7CA1BE|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = Poisoned Apple\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|18|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The news that a new player arrived was given to the players. Ray was told she would be able to see the results of the Opinion Poll from last episode. From the results, she could choose one person to go on a date with in the Blue Room. She decided to go on a date with Lorayne.\n*'''Game (\"Jogo da Verdade\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Game of Truth\")''': One at a time, players would ask another player a question. The player who received the question could either answer the question truthfully or complete a dare produced by The Circle.\nAfter the game finished, the ratings opened. As the new player, Ray could rate the other players but could not be rated. When the rating results were revealed, it was announced that the lowest rated player would immediately get blocked from The Circle. The lowest rated player was Gaybol. Gaybol went to visit JP's apartment.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Poisoned Apple|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062051?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C4%2Cb57813d8-ab51-4a8d-9ce3-7e0eace81d9a-28553664%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=18 March 2020|season=1|number=5}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = Blue Room\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|18|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = It was revealed that another player would be blocked that night. JP and Lorayne, after receiving first and second place respectively, became Influencers and headed to the Blue Room. JP and Lorayne decided to block Lucas. Loma headed to Marina's apartment, where she revealed herself to be catfishing as Lucas.\n\nThe next morning, the newsfeed was updating with video messages from Gaybol and Loma, revealing that Loma was a catfish.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Blue Room|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062052?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C5%2C5c617a0e-8c23-4ab4-9831-3fe741157209-63757635%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=18 March 2020|season=1|number=6}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = The Circle Cup\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|18|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Raf joined The Circle, playing as his best friend, Ana. After he created Ana's profile, his profile became public, and the players were able to see Ana's profile. Then, The Circle Chat opened, allowing Raf to make his first impression as Ana.\n*'''Game (\"Mentes Brilhantes\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Brilliant Minds\")''': Split into two teams, the Pink Team and the Blue Team, will each select a player for a given category. The player will have to answer a question that pertains to the category. The team to have the most correct answers won a pizza party; the losing team will be revoked of their access to ''The Circle'' for the night. After they tied, it went to a tiebreaker question. The Blue Team answered the last question correctly, granting Ray, Lorayne, JP, Lucas, and Marcel a pizza party.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Circle Cup|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062053?trackId=14277281&tctx=0%2C6%2Ca395243a-a75d-4c23-bf8b-1274bd0f1230-94393368%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=18 March 2020|season=1|number=7}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Painting Truths\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|18|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The ratings opened, and, as the new player, Ana could not be rated but she could rate the other players.\n*'''Game''': Each player received a canvas and painting supplies. They were told to use the painting supplies to create a painting for a specific player given by The Circle. The players could paint whatever they wanted, as long as it was directed to that player.\nThe results were revealed. Lucas & Marcel and Dumaresq came in first and second respectively, making them the Influencers. They made their way to the Blue Room to make their decision on who to block. However, the Influencers were given the power to save one person of their choosing before deliberating on who to block. Lucas & Marcel saved Ray and Dumaresq saved Marina.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Painting Truths|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062054?trackId=14277283&tctx=0%2C7%2Cfed8d000-e8bb-4464-bd6a-14eed00f9c00-87099275%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=18 March 2020|season=1|number=8}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|p=Week 3|c=#7CA1BE|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = Pool Party\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|25|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = After it came down to the three vulnerable players, Lorayne, Akel, and JP, Akel was blocked from The Circle. He was allowed to visit another player's apartment, and he chose to visit Lorayne.\n\nThe next morning, a new player, Renan, entered The Circle. He was allowed to send breakfast to another female player. He chose Lorayne. After the breakfast, the newsfeed was updated with Akel's video,  in which he was revealed to be real, but admitted to lying about his age and profession. That night, there was a \"festa\" or party because Renan was the last player to enter The Circle; however, immediately after the party, the ratings opened. Renan, being the newest player, was allowed to rate the other players, but he couldn't get rated. When the ratings were supposed to be announced, The Circle revealed that the highest rated player became the Superinfluencer, so there was no need to reveal the ratings. Lucas & Marcel got an alert saying that they had become the Superinfluencer, and they would have to tell the player they chose to block about their decision in person. They made their way to the apartment.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Pool Party|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062055?trackId=13752289&tctx=0%2C8%2Ca423bf5c-0ba8-4a5d-9c1a-f75fc24fd306-83442689%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=25 March 2020|season=1|number=9}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = Fatal Visit\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|25|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Lucas & Marcel decided to block Lorayne. Since Lucas & Marcel had to visit her apartment, Lorayne was not able to meet another player face-to-face. The next morning, the newsfeed was updated with a message from Lorayne. After the message, Lucas & Marcel decided to tell everyone that they were the Superinfluencer.\n*'''Game (\"Meu Maior Rival\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"My Biggest Rival\")''': One at a time, players had to announce their biggest rival to all of the other players and explain why they should beat their rival at the finale. The rival would then get a chance to send a response.\nThat night, the ratings opened. Everyone was able to be rated. Soon after, the ratings were revealed, and Dumaresq and JP became Influencers, placing first and second respectively. However, the Influencers were not allowed to deliberate. Instead, each Influencer took turns saving one player until only one player remained. The player that was not saved would be blocked. Dumaresq went first, since he was rated higher than JP, and saved Raf. JP then saved Lucas & Marcel, and Dumaresq saved Marina. It came down to either Ray or Renan. JP saved Ray, meaning Renan was immediately blocked.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Fatal Visit|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062056?trackId=13752289&tctx=0%2C9%2Ca423bf5c-0ba8-4a5d-9c1a-f75fc24fd306-83442689%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=25 March 2020|season=1|number=10}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n| Title           = Candid Questions\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|25|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Renan, after getting blocked, went to visit Raf at his apartment. There, he was revealed to be a catfish.\n*'''Game (\"A \u00daltima Bomba\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"The Last Bomb\")''': One at a time, players anonymously asked question to a player of their choosing, and they must answer the question truthfully.\nImmediately after the game, the ratings opened. Soon after the ratings were revealed, and JP and Dumaresq became Influencers, placing first and second respectively. They made their way to the Blue Room and deliberated on who to block. They chose to block Raf. After he was blocked, Raf decided to visit Dumaresq's apartment, revealing he was a catfish. After Raf left, the players were informed that they were the finalists of ''The Circle Brazil''. To celebrate, they had a party. Then, each player received a video from their families.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Candid Questions|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81220247?trackId=13752289&tctx=0%2C10%2Ca423bf5c-0ba8-4a5d-9c1a-f75fc24fd306-83442689%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=25 March 2020|season=1|number=11}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = The Final Meeting\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|25|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The next day, the newsfeed was updated with a goodbye message from Raf, revealing to everyone that he was a catfish. the ratings opened. The players had to rate each other from first to fourth as the final rating of ''The Circle Brazil''.\n\nThe players, as part of finale night, all went to one room to meet each other face-to-face for the first time during the whole game. JP entered the room. Then, Lucas & Marcel entered the room, revealing they were a catfish to JP. Soon after, all the other players entered and found out Lucas & Marcel were a catfish.\n\nOn finale night, Giovanna Ewbank talked with the blocked players and interviewed the finalists before revealing the final ratings. Marina placed first and became the winner of ''The Circle Brazil''. Ray got second place, JP got third place, Dumaresq got fourth place, and Lucas & Marcel got fifth place.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Final Meeting|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81220248?trackId=13752289&tctx=0%2C11%2Ca423bf5c-0ba8-4a5d-9c1a-f75fc24fd306-83442689%2C%2C|series=The Circle Brazil|network=[[Netflix]]|date=25 March 2020|season=1|number=12}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 7CA1BE\n}}\n}}\n\n== Background ==\n=== Concept ===\nTim Harcourt is the creative director of [[Studio Lambert]], which produces the British and American versions of the show. Harcourt wondered what a [[Reality competition|reality show]] would look like if the people never met face-to-face. He had also been considering the idea of a [[bird's-eye view]]-style documentary of an apartment building, seeing into each of their lives. He began to work on ''The Circle'' after hearing that [[Channel 4]] was looking for a reality-show format centered on social media.<ref name=\"insider\">{{cite web |last1=Smallman |first1=Etan |title=Inside 'The Circle,' Reality TV Gets a Social Media Filter |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/29/arts/television/the-circle-netflix.html |website=nytimes.com |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=30 December 2019 |location=London, United Kingdom |date=29 December 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Development ===\n[[The Circle (British TV series)|The British version]] of the show premiered in 2018, and was renewed for its second season a few months after the first season ended.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tutton|first1=Charlotte|title=The Circle season 2 confirmed as Channel 4 series returns with a HUGE twist|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/tv/1541465/the-circle-season-2-channel-4-series-return-new-twists-live-episode-how-long-on-prize-money-win|website=OK! Magazine|accessdate=19 January 2019 |date=18 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ling|first1=Thomas|title=The Circle series 2 confirmed \u2013 but there are going to be some changes|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-01-18/the-circle-series-2-channel-4-confirmed-how-to-apply|website=Radio Times|accessdate=19 January 2019|language=en}}</ref> After the first season was [[Channel 4]]'s \"youngest profiling\" show in six years, according to the British TV industry magazine ''[[Broadcast (magazine)|Broadcast]]'', talks began of international versions.<ref name=\"insider\"/> On October 8, 2018, [[Netflix]] announced its partnership with [[All3Media]] to create three international versions of ''The Circle'' on Netflix, including the American version. Brandon Reigg, Netflix's Vice Principal of Unscripted Content, stated, \"We think the show's combination of modern social media interaction and competition will captivate Netflix members around the world, in multiple languages, and we're delighted to partner with Studio Lambert and Motion to produce these three new local versions.\"<ref name=\"adaptation\">{{cite web|url=https://media.netflix.com/en/press-releases/netflix-to-adapt-uk-unscripted-sensation-the-circle-with-three-local-versions-for-countries-around-the-world|title=Netflix to Adapt UK Unscripted Sensation ''The Circle'' with Three Local Versions for Countries Around the World|date=8 October 2018|publisher=Netflix Media Center|location=Hollywood, California|url-status=live|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Production == \n=== Casting ===\nIn an interview with ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', Tim Harcourt, one of the executive producers for [[Studio Lambert]], stated that ''The Circle'' format and premise allowed the casting team to search for all different kinds of people. He noted how the casting contrasted from casts on show like ''[[Real Housewives]]'' or ''[[Jersey Shore (TV series)|Jersey Shore]]'' and how those shows are \"all one gang of quite similar characters.\"<ref name=\"variety interview\">{{cite web |last1=Turchiano |first1=Danielle |title='The Circle' Boss on Connecting 'People Who Otherwise Might Not Have Come into Contact with Each Other' \u2014 And Catfishing |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/features/the-circle-netflix-american-tim-harcourt-catfish-interview-1203449625/ |website=variety.com |publisher=Variety |accessdate=2 January 2020 |date=1 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> He explained how there was no set cast for the show until it was over. The first eight players to enter were all predetermined and planned, but everything after that was all luck to whoever got on. Harcourt stated that the production team would decide who would be the right fit depending on who just left the game, acknowledging that with thirteen contestants, not all who were possible players end up on the show at all.<ref name=\"variety interview\"/>\n\n=== The Circle app ===\nEach apartment that the players live in is plastered with screens in every room in order for the players be able to hold conversations with other players as they go about their everyday lives. Each player starts out the game by creating a profile. This includes sharing their age, [[relationship status]], a short [[biography|bio]], and one photo to use as their [[Avatar (computing)|profile picture]]. Everyday, the players are allowed to share a status update, explaining their thoughts for the day. Sometimes, either through rewards or passing a certain milestone, the players are allowed to upload another photo to their profile.<ref name=\"variety interview 1\"/> However, the main purpose of The Circle is to be the only way players can communicate with each other.<ref name=\"variety interview 1\"/>\n\nAt several points during the game, usually every episode, The Circle has the players play a [[minigame]] so that they can get to know their fellow players better. Tim Harcourt of [[Studio Lambert]] says that \"some games were really good for bonding them, some were really good for them learning about each other, some were good for testing who's a catfish, some could have been more divisive.\"<ref name=\"variety interview 1\"/>\n\nAt certain points during the show, there would be a rating. Players would have to rate each other from first to last by using The Circle and announcing the players they want in each placement. Then, The Circle would average all the placements for each players and create an average for each player. Depending on how high or low their average placement was, the player's ranking would determine if they became in influencer or not. An influencer is usually the two people who get first and second place at the ratings. The influencers would head to the hangout and discuss over The Circle which person to block.<ref name=\"variety interview 1\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Fallo |first1=Julie |title=The Circle: US Version Has a Shot at Succeeding From All the Right Changes |url=https://screenrant.com/circle-us-version-success-changes/ |website=screenrant.com |publisher=Screen Rant |accessdate=15 January 2020 |date=3 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nThe Circle Brazil was filmed in Fall 2019, after the [[The Circle (American TV series)|American version's first season]] and [[The Circle (British TV series)|the British version]]'s [[The Circle (British series 2)|second season]]. Filming took place in the same [[Salford|Salford, England]] apartment building that was used for the American version and second season of the British version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/how-the-circle-works-creator-tim-harcourt.html|title=The Circle\u2019s Creator Guides Us Through the Show\u2019s Beautiful Web of Lies|last=Haylock|first=Zoe|date=2020-01-21|website=Vulture|language=en-us|accessdate=22 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Apartment building ===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:The Circle apartments.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|The apartment building used in ''The Circle''. The 82-foot diameter [[LED lamp|LED]] circle on the front of the building and the lit up rooftop lounge on the roof can be seen.]] -->\nAs was the same for all versions of ''The Circle'', the first season of ''The Circle Brazil'' was shot entirely in an apartment building in [[Salford|Salford, England]].<ref name=\"apartment building\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a29522354/the-circle-future-series-american-brazilian-versions-filming-location/|title=The Circle may be coming back sooner than you think|last=Anderton|first=Joe|date=|website=[[Digital Spy]]|url-status=live}}</ref> The apartment building is always prepared with twelve furnished and ready-to-use apartments for the players to live in.<ref name=\"the circle works\">{{cite web |last1=Haylock |first1=Zoe |title=The Circle's Creator Guides Us Through the Show's Beautiful Web of Lies |url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/how-the-circle-works-creator-tim-harcourt.html |website=vulture.com |publisher=Vulture |accessdate=23 January 2020 |language=English |date=21 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The building also has an exercise room and a rooftop lounge, which are also outfitted with cameras and television screens.<ref name=\"apartment tour\">{{cite web |author1=Netflix |title=Go Inside The Circle Apartment Complex with Michelle Buteau \u2013 Netflix |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=16TGiQZQw4Y |website=youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=23 January 2020 |language=English |date=14 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> One room in the building, called \"the testimonial room,\" is the room players go to after they are blocked to create their goodbye video to the remaining players.<ref name=\"seventeen tour\">{{cite web |last1=Fuentes |first1=Tamara |title=Exclusive: Go Behind the Scenes of \"The Circle\" and Check Out the Apartments |url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/movies-tv/a30503978/netflix-the-circle-behind-the-scenes-apartments-exclusive/ |website=seventeen.com |publisher=Seventeen |accessdate=23 January 2020 |language=English |date=14 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> On the outside of the building is a large, lit up circle made of a roughly 82-foot (25-meter) diameter aluminum track with [[LED lamp|LED lights]] strung through and around the circle.<ref name=\"the circle works\"/>\n\nOpposite the apartment building was the control room, which was previously a college campus that became disused.<ref name=\"the circle works\"/> At any time in the control room, there were between twenty and thirty producers and camera operators working, recording, and sending all the messages from The Circle.<ref name=\"the circle works\"/>\n\n=== Release ===\nOn 27 January 2020, a teaser for the Brazilian version was released, revealing the premiere date to be 11 March 2020.<ref name=\"teaser\"/> Then, on 27 February, [[Netflix]] released the trailer for the first season, revealing the prize amount to be {{BRL|300000|link=yes}} ({{USD|67000}}).<ref>{{cite tweet|user=NetflixBrasil|number=1233046490626609152|date=27 February 2020|title=N\u00e3o sei quem eu vou amar e quem eu vou odiar, s\u00f3 sei que quero assistir logo. Apresentado pela @gewbank, The Circle Brasil estreia dia 11 de mar\u00e7o.}}</ref>\n\n== Results and elimination ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|+ <big>'''Color Key'''</big>\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was blocked.\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightgreen; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was an influencer.\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FBF373; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was immune from being blocked.\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:100%; font-size:90%; line-he